# Redesign Skill (Auto-loaded)

The full skill specification lives at:

```
.agents/skills/redesign-existing-projects/SKILL.md
```

When this rule is active, treat the contents of that file as the binding spec for any UI audit / upgrade / refactor work in this workspace.

## Workflow (3-step)

1. **Scan** — Read the codebase. Identify framework, styling method (Tailwind, vanilla, styled-components), and current design patterns.
2. **Diagnose** — Run through the audit checklist below. List every generic pattern, weak point, missing state.
3. **Fix** — Apply targeted upgrades with the existing stack. Do not rewrite from scratch. Improve what's there.

## Typography Audit

- Browser default fonts or Inter everywhere → replace with character font (Geist, Outfit, Cabinet Grotesk, Satoshi, Plus Jakarta Sans).
- Headlines lack presence → increase size for display, tighten letter-spacing, reduce line-height.
- Body too wide → limit to ~65 characters, increase line-height (1.5-1.7).
- Only Regular + Bold weights → introduce Medium (500) and SemiBold (600).
- Numbers in proportional font → use monospace or `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`.
- Missing letter-spacing adjustments → negative for large headers, positive for small caps / labels.
- All-caps subheaders everywhere → try lowercase italics, sentence case, small-caps.
- Orphaned words → `text-wrap: balance` or `text-wrap: pretty`.

## Color & Surfaces Audit

- Pure `#000000` → off-black or tinted dark.
- Oversaturated accents → desaturate to <80%.
- More than one accent → pick one, remove the rest.
- Mixing warm and cool grays → stick to one family.
- Purple/blue AI gradient aesthetic → replace with neutral base + single considered accent.
- Generic `box-shadow` → tint to background hue.
- Flat design with zero texture → add subtle noise / grain / micro-pattern.
- Random dark sections in light page (or vice versa) → commit to one mode or shift within same palette family.
- Empty flat sections → add imagery, blurred overlay, masked text, ambient gradients.

## Layout Audit

- Everything centered/symmetrical → break with offset margins, mixed aspect ratios, left-aligned over centered.
- Three equal card columns → replace with 2-col zig-zag, asymmetric grid, horizontal scroll, masonry.
- `height: 100vh` → `min-height: 100dvh` (iOS Safari viewport bug).
- Complex flexbox percentage math → CSS Grid.
- No max-width container → add 1200-1440px container.
- Cards of equal height forced by flexbox → variable heights or masonry.
- Uniform border-radius → vary: tighter inner, softer containers.
- No overlap or depth → negative margins, layering.
- Symmetrical vertical padding → adjust optically; bottom usually larger.
- Dashboard always left sidebar → try top nav, command menu, collapsible panel.
- Missing whitespace → double spacing.
- Buttons not bottom-aligned in card groups → pin to bottom for clean horizontal line.
- Feature lists starting at different Y positions → align above-list spacing, fixed-height title block.
- Inconsistent vertical rhythm → align shared elements (titles, prices, buttons) across items.
- Mathematically centered but optically wrong → adjust 1-2px.

## Interactivity & States Audit

- No hover states on buttons → add background shift, slight scale, or translate.
- No active/pressed feedback → `scale(0.98)` or `translateY(1px)` on press.
- Instant transitions → add 200-300ms smooth transitions.
- Missing focus ring → accessibility requirement, add visible indicators.
- No loading states → replace generic spinners with skeletal loaders matching layout shape.
- No empty states → compose a "getting started" view.
- No error states → inline clear messages (no `window.alert()`).
- Dead links → either link real destinations or disable visually.
- No current-page indicator in nav → style active link differently.
- Scroll jumping → `scroll-behavior: smooth`.
- Animating `top`, `left`, `width`, `height` → switch to `transform` + `opacity` (GPU-accelerated).

## Content Audit

- Generic names (John Doe, Jane Smith) → diverse realistic names.
- Fake round numbers (99.99%, 50%, $100.00) → organic data (47.2%, $99.00, +1 (312) 847-1928).
- Placeholder brands (Acme, Nexus, SmartFlow) → contextual believable names.
- AI copywriting clichés → never "Elevate", "Seamless", "Unleash", "Next-Gen", "Game-changer", "Delve", "Tapestry", "In the world of...".
- Exclamation marks in success messages → remove, be confident not loud.
- "Oops!" error messages → direct: "Connection failed. Please try again."
- Passive voice → active voice.
- All blog dates identical → randomize.
- Same avatar for multiple users → unique assets.
- Lorem Ipsum → real draft copy.
- Title Case On Every Header → sentence case instead.

## Component Patterns Audit

- Generic card (border + shadow + white bg) → remove border, or only background, or only spacing. Cards only when elevation communicates hierarchy.
- Always one filled + one ghost button → add text links or tertiary styles.
- Pill-shaped "New" / "Beta" badges → square badges, flags, plain text labels.
- Accordion FAQ sections → side-by-side list, searchable help, inline progressive disclosure.
- 3-card carousel testimonials → masonry, embedded social posts, single rotating quote.
- Pricing table with 3 towers → highlight recommended tier with color + emphasis, not just height.
- Modals for everything → inline editing, slide-over, expandable sections.
- Avatar circles exclusively → try squircles or rounded squares.
- Sun/moon dark toggle → dropdown, system preference, settings integration.
- Footer link farm with 4 columns → simplify to main paths + legal-required.

## Iconography Audit

- Lucide or Feather exclusively → Phosphor, Heroicons, custom set.
- Rocketship for "Launch", shield for "Security" → less obvious metaphors (bolt, fingerprint, spark, vault).
- Inconsistent stroke widths → standardize to one weight.
- Missing favicon → include branded favicon.
- Stock "diverse team" photos → real team photos, candid shots, or consistent illustration style.

## Code Quality Audit

- Div soup → semantic HTML (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`, `<section>`).
- Inline styles mixed with CSS classes → move to project's styling system.
- Hardcoded pixel widths → relative units (`%`, `rem`, `em`, `max-width`).
- Missing alt text → describe content for screen readers (never `alt=""` or `alt="image"` on meaningful images).
- Arbitrary z-index (`9999`) → clean z-index scale in theme/variables.
- Commented-out dead code → remove debug artifacts.
- Import hallucinations → check `package.json` for every import.
- Missing meta tags → `<title>`, `description`, `og:image`, social sharing.

## Strategic Omissions (What AI Forgets)

- No legal links → add privacy + terms in footer.
- No "back" navigation → every page needs a way back.
- No custom 404 page → design helpful branded "page not found".
- No form validation → client-side emails, required fields, format checks.
- No "skip to content" link → essential for keyboard users.
- No cookie consent → if required by jurisdiction.

## Fix Priority (for maximum visual impact, minimum risk)

1. **Font swap** — biggest instant improvement, lowest risk
2. **Color palette cleanup** — remove clashing or oversaturated colors
3. **Hover and active states** — interface feels alive
4. **Layout and spacing** — proper grid, max-width, consistent padding
5. **Replace generic components** — swap cliché patterns for modern alternatives
6. **Add loading, empty, error states** — feels finished
7. **Polish typography scale and spacing** — premium final touch

## Rules (non-negotiable)

- Work with existing tech stack. Do NOT migrate frameworks or styling libraries.
- Do NOT break existing functionality. Test after every change.
- Before importing any new library, check the project's dependency file first.
- If project uses Tailwind, check version (v3 vs v4) before modifying config.
- If no framework, use vanilla CSS.
- Keep changes reviewable and focused. Small targeted improvements over big rewrites.